track_notes: Easy 10 pointer; some lake on the way to summit; last part is a bit slope but not difficult

This trac is anticlockwise to reach 2 summits. Not too difficult, not too long, therefore you must have good health, good shoes and lot of water in hot wx. Also take some rain clothes, because it is hight mountains, the landscape is wonderfull, plenty room to park and for antenna.
This is a pleasant way to activate this summit; the ridges is very nice offering very hight mountain walk
2 summits cime des Lauses and Belletz (before 2017)

Starting from the parking at the end of the small road, you will surely found a place for the car if you come early as the place is crowded in summer time. In winter the road is closed because of the snow. The walk is easy until you reach the Col Ferriere; since this point you must go on the left, the slope is a bit hard but no long. Plenty room for antenna on summit. If you look around, the other summits on the crest look higher; in fact there are not (perspective effect). Enjoy!
